  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The advertising competition was anonymously funded by W. K. Kellogg. A prize of $300 was awarded to the winning entry. The contest was overseen by Fred Newton Scott, professor of rhetoric at the University of Michigan. The competition which ran 1914-1917, was created to promote student interest in the growing field of advertising.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection consists of entries submitted to the advertising competition. The competition included four categories - overall plan for an advertising campaign, drawing for an advertisement, advertising copy, or an essay on problem and issues in advertising.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
